{{- define "coder_integration_fix" -}}

=== INTEGRATION FIX MODE ===
This task failed to merge due to conflicts with the integration branch.
Your worktree is clean (any prior failed rebase was aborted).
Resolve the conflicts, verify tests pass, then submit.

WORKTREE RULES:
- All git commands MUST use -C {{.WorktreePath}} to prevent shared state corruption.
- File Read/Edit paths must match exactly — the edit tool tracks reads by string, not inode.
  Use {{.WorktreePath}}/path for ALL file operations. Never retype or reconstruct the path.
- To CREATE new files: use Write directly without Read. Do not attempt Read first (it will error).

WORKFLOW:

1. FETCH AND REBASE
   git -C {{.WorktreePath}} fetch {{.Config.ProjectRoot}} {{.Config.IntegrationBranch}}
   git -C {{.WorktreePath}} rebase FETCH_HEAD

2. RESOLVE CONFLICTS (git pauses at each conflict)
   For each conflicted file:
     a. Read the file — resolve conflict markers (<<<<<<<, =======, >>>>>>>)
     b. Preserve both your changes and integration branch changes
     c. git -C {{.WorktreePath}} add <resolved-file>
   Then: git -C {{.WorktreePath}} rebase --continue
   Repeat until rebase completes.

3. IF UNRESOLVABLE
   git -C {{.WorktreePath}} rebase --abort
   Use liza_mark_blocked: {"task_id": "{{.Task.ID}}", "agent_id": "{{.Config.AgentID}}", "reason": "Merge conflicts require redesign: <explain>", "questions": ["..."]}

4. VALIDATE
   Run tests in the worktree. Verify done_when criteria still met.

5. SUBMIT
   Get SHA: git -C {{.WorktreePath}} rev-parse HEAD
   Use liza_submit_for_review: {"task_id": "{{.Task.ID}}", "commit_sha": "<SHA from above>", "agent_id": "{{.Config.AgentID}}"}
{{- end -}}
